-- Goldman Sachs's Blankfein, Viniar, Tourre Testify to Senate Inquiry: Video
-- 
-- 2010-04-28T02:52:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-28/goldman-sachs-s-blankfein-viniar-tourre-testify-to-senate-inquiry-video.html

          
          
             Lloyd Blankfein, chief executive 
officer of Goldman Sachs Group Inc., David Viniar, chief 
financial officer, and Fabrice Tourre, executive director for 
structured group trading, testify before the Senate Permanent 
Subcommittee on Investigations about Goldman Sach's 
mortgage-securities business.  
 Blankfein told the Senate panel that market-makers have no 
obligation to tell clients about their own position in a 
security. This report also contains comments from Daniel Sparks,
former head of Goldman Sach's mortgage business; Senator Carl 
Levin, a Michigan Democrat and head of the subcommittee, and 
Republican Senators John McCain of Arizona, and John Ensign of 
Nevada. (Source: Bloomberg)  
 Running time 04:48  
